1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:03,003
***Subtitles Ardarvin & Mayumi***

2
00:00:03,479 --> 00:00:09,342
'Celebrity Ranking Check 2026: New Year Special'

3
00:00:09,773 --> 00:00:16,182
It begins! 2026 Celebrity Ranking Check Special!

4
00:00:16,207 --> 00:00:19,395
Start your year with your first big laugh on this show.

5
00:00:19,419 --> 00:00:23,498
Kick off a wonderful year in the best mood possible.

6
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:26,626
Do you think this is going to be pretty difficult?

7
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:30,236
The six checks that top-class celebrities should normally ace

8
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:34,434
are extra tough this year, with one surprise after another.

9
00:00:34,459 --> 00:00:37,685
A famous actor has a sword fight

10
00:00:37,697 --> 00:00:40,078
A legend sings a classic hit,

11
00:00:40,090 --> 00:00:45,142
and the nonstop shocking checks have emotions exploding everywhere

12
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:47,046
tears for some,

13
00:00:47,211 --> 00:00:49,175
'We did it!' for others!

14
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,355
Mega-level bombshell moments just keep coming.

15
00:00:52,380 --> 00:00:54,438
There is literally nothing but highlights.

16
00:00:56,823 --> 00:00:58,837
GACKT-sama is on an 81-win streak

17
00:00:58,849 --> 00:01:01,227
Who dares to face him this year?

18
00:01:01,421 --> 00:01:05,698
All right, here we go!

19
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:19,620
'Celebrity Ranking Check 2026.'

20
00:01:19,645 --> 00:01:23,792
Competing are top-tier celebrities from all walks of entertainment.

21
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:27,274
Let us introduce the eight teams.

22
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:28,329
First up,

23
00:01:28,354 --> 00:01:31,240
A man who has always stayed at the forefront of the industry,

24
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:36,162
Go Hiromi-sama, who will celebrate the 55th anniversary of his debut next year,

25
00:01:36,187 --> 00:01:40,455
And the artist who blew up with her 'sexy and cool' songs and performances,

26
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:43,577
Kumi Koda-sama, marking the 25th anniversary of her debut this year.

27
00:01:43,589 --> 00:01:46,406
It's an anniversary year for them both.

28
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:52,286
Team Anniversary: Hiromi Go & Kumi Koda!

29
00:01:52,313 --> 00:01:54,201
Let's have fun with it.

30
00:01:54,225 --> 00:01:55,619
But, Hiromi-san, you know,

31
00:01:55,644 --> 00:01:56,493
it's fine.

32
00:01:56,518 --> 00:01:58,324
I mean, as a sort of celebration,

33
00:01:58,349 --> 00:01:59,786
I heard it's 70, right?

34
00:01:59,811 --> 00:02:01,220
You still look so youthful.

35
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:03,756
So I really want us to win as a birthday gift.

36
00:02:03,781 --> 00:02:08,194
We've prepared a practice question to predict how they'll do today.

37
00:02:08,219 --> 00:02:12,075
The warm-up challenge for Team Anniversary is popcorn.

38
00:02:12,099 --> 00:02:14,242
All you have to do is pick the expensive one, A.

39
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:17,101
My face must look ridiculous right now.

40
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:19,775
I've got no clue with something like this.

41
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,755
I'll start with A.

42
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:24,435
These two are entering a very special anniversary year.

43
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:29,171
They really can't afford to miss such an easy pre-game question.

44
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:33,228
Their answers are...

45
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:35,028
One, two...

46
00:02:35,053 --> 00:02:35,833
Okay!

47
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,029
Split!

48
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,655
Then let's go with the one on the right.

49
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,908
Yeah.

50
00:02:42,006 --> 00:02:43,857
Wrong!

51
00:02:45,218 --> 00:02:48,060
It's fine, it's fine, it's fine.

52
00:02:48,086 --> 00:02:51,110
Just do whatever you want.

53
00:02:51,135 --> 00:02:54,520
Kumi-chan, never ever lose that innocent, free-spirited side of you.

54
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,995
Be bold and own it.

55
00:02:56,021 --> 00:02:56,877
Got it.

56
00:02:57,308 --> 00:02:58,711
Uh, Hiromi...

57
00:02:58,736 --> 00:03:03,816
Calling Hiromi-sama just 'Hiromi' is a bold innocence

58
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:07,937
But if a musician messes this one up,

58
00:03:07,962 --> 00:03:09,464
they should probably just retire, right?

59
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:10,775
Retire!

60
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,292
Don't say that!

61
00:03:13,826 --> 00:03:18,840
Will the wrong answer mean an early New Year retirement?

62
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:23,111
Yesterday's Red and White Song Battle was a huge success,

63
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:26,839
and Fruits Zipper are exploding in popularity as a national idol group.

64
00:03:26,864 --> 00:03:31,477
Five members from the group are joining us today.

65
00:03:31,501 --> 00:03:35,020
Who do you think will be the key member?

66
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:38,410
When it comes to food,

66
00:03:38,422 --> 00:03:40,475
Chinsei-san's the one.

67
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:41,688
I love food.

68
00:03:41,713 --> 00:03:45,140
The check for Fruits Zipper is seaweed.

69
00:03:45,165 --> 00:03:49,394
By the way, for all the warm-up questions, the correct answer is always A.

70
00:03:49,419 --> 00:03:51,431
And the answer is...

71
00:03:55,678 --> 00:03:57,465
Everyone got it right!

72
00:03:57,490 --> 00:03:59,043
Yay!

73
00:03:59,068 --> 00:04:00,060
We got this!

74
00:04:00,085 --> 00:04:01,055
Pretty good start, right?

75
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,455
This is awesome!

76
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,585
We can totally do this!

77
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:06,168
We're first-class!

78
00:04:06,193 --> 00:04:09,791
Whenever something good happens, our president always ________

79
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:10,850
Don't say that!

80
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:18,566
Fruits Zipper are out to leave a serious impression on this year's Ranking Check.

81
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,127
These girls are really sweet.

82
00:04:21,151 --> 00:04:23,371
Go on, Fruits Chuck!

83
00:04:23,396 --> 00:04:25,365
Zipper!

84
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:27,967
Next up,

85
00:04:27,992 --> 00:04:31,972
A slightly out-of-sync couple's offbeat, heart-throbbing love story.

86
00:04:31,997 --> 00:04:36,776
From the drama '50-Minute Lover,' premiering Sunday, January 18,

87
00:04:36,801 --> 00:04:39,720
Kei Inoo-sama from Hey! Say! JUMP,

88
00:04:39,745 --> 00:04:41,233
Kimura Tae-sama

89
00:04:41,258 --> 00:04:44,125
Takahashi Mitsuomi-sama.

90
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:46,376
Their warm-up question is...

91
00:04:46,401 --> 00:04:47,620
miso.

92
00:04:47,645 --> 00:04:50,280
The answers they gave are...

93
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:54,096
A clearly has a bit more

94
00:04:54,121 --> 00:04:57,434
depth to it

95
00:04:57,460 --> 00:04:59,197
For me, it tasted a bit salty.

96
00:04:59,222 --> 00:05:01,575
Yeah, I found it salty too.

97
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,715
Um, I'll go with B.

98
00:05:03,746 --> 00:05:06,153
OK, then let's say B.

99
00:05:06,178 --> 00:05:08,803
With the drama leads putting their heads together...

100
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,492
Buzzer!

101
00:05:11,113 --> 00:05:15,495
See? That wasn't so bad, was it?

102
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,349
You're right.

103
00:05:16,373 --> 00:05:20,753
In the main game, there will definitely be food questions too.

104
00:05:20,778 --> 00:05:24,090
Mitsuomi is an amazing cook, that's really his specialty.

105
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:30,063
So when it comes to taste, he's going to be seriously strong.

106
00:05:30,088 --> 00:05:32,098
Just, when it comes to miso...

107
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:35,175
I am not making miso-flavored madeleines.

108
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,502
Let me make that clear right now.

109
00:05:36,803 --> 00:05:42,595
Takahashi Mitsuomi, who's has already made a mistake, is actually a key player on this team?

110
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:44,877
Will he be okay?

111
00:05:44,902 --> 00:05:49,682
Thanks for telling me nothing useful.

112
00:05:49,707 --> 00:05:52,226
Next up,

113
00:05:52,251 --> 00:05:59,192
Team Yoshimoto: Atsushi Tamura and the two members of Batteries, who blew up in popularity last year.

114
00:05:59,217 --> 00:06:04,806
The warm-up question: a premium butter you spread on bread crusts and eat.

115
00:06:04,831 --> 00:06:09,039
The wrong answer is something totally different: margarine.

116
00:06:09,394 --> 00:06:11,442
Their answer is...

117
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:13,675
Whaaat?

118
00:06:13,989 --> 00:06:15,559
'B'?

119
00:06:15,571 --> 00:06:17,535
As in 'B' for 'butter'?

120
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,321
No! How stupid do you think we are?

121
00:06:20,346 --> 00:06:22,340
On this one, you should go with me.

122
00:06:22,365 --> 00:06:23,523
You sure about that?

123
00:06:23,548 --> 00:06:26,928
For real, I use really good butter at home.

124
00:06:26,952 --> 00:06:28,774
At home? You should have led with that.

125
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,148
Since I use good butter at home, it's this one.

126
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:33,352
And... wrong.

127
00:06:35,521 --> 00:06:38,955
Totally useless! Go throw that 'good butter' away.

128
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:40,775
So this is just hopeless now, huh?

129
00:06:40,799 --> 00:06:41,900
Is it really hopeless?

130
00:06:41,924 --> 00:06:46,139
But when it counts, I'm crazy strong, so if it's the real thing...

131
00:06:46,164 --> 00:06:48,259
No, trust me in the real thing.

132
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:51,577
Seriously, I pull off stuff even I can't believe.

133
00:06:52,047 --> 00:06:53,843
You sure about that?

134
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:56,749
I really do better in the actual show.

135
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,775
The entertainment world's most fastidious man.

136
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:04,690
Batteries decide to trust their veteran senior, Atsushi Tamura, and follow his lead.

137
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:09,255
But a shocking falling-out leaves them in a state beyond repair.

138
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:12,165
This is a total disaster.

139
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:17,937
And what everyone is most curious about is...

140
00:07:17,962 --> 00:07:22,015
Nobody misses a question this easy.

141
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:26,746
I honestly don't get how you get this wrong.

142
00:07:26,771 --> 00:07:33,719
GACKT-sama, currently on a record-breaking personal streak of 81 straight wins.

143
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:38,157
Who on earth will be his partner this time?

144
00:07:38,182 --> 00:07:44,439
One day in October, a message arrived from GACKT-sama to the show producer.

145
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:48,788
'It's been a while. This is GACKT.'

146
00:07:48,813 --> 00:07:52,755
'I have something to discuss regarding this year's Ranking Check appearance.'

147
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:56,402
'Could you come to Malaysia next Wednesday?'

148
00:07:56,804 --> 00:08:00,275
That's right, GACKT-sama lives in Malaysia.

149
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:04,742
He summoned us to Malaysia as casually as if it were a meeting in downtown Tokyo.

150
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,905
But this had to be something important.

151
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,738
'Understood.'

152
00:08:09,762 --> 00:08:11,690
'I'll come.'

153
00:08:11,716 --> 00:08:17,463
What could this be about?

154
00:08:17,487 --> 00:08:19,999
About seven hours by plane from Japan.

155
00:08:20,024 --> 00:08:22,935
After arriving in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, we

156
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:26,405
headed straight to GACKT-sama's mansion.

157
00:08:27,039 --> 00:08:29,702
Beyond these tight security gates

158
00:08:29,734 --> 00:08:32,702
lies GACKT-sama's residence.

159
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:38,344
Over nine hours after leaving Japan,

160
00:08:38,369 --> 00:08:42,031
we can finally hear what GACKT-sama has to say.

161
00:08:43,294 --> 00:08:47,995
This fortress-like estate is GACKT-sama's home.

162
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:50,763
Just getting to the front door is already a struggle.

163
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:53,824
And finally...

164
00:09:01,158 --> 00:09:05,074
We were greeted by GACKT-sama's local staff.

165
00:09:05,101 --> 00:09:07,388
Um, is GACKT-sama here?

166
00:09:07,413 --> 00:09:10,155
GACKT is currently out on business.

167
00:09:10,180 --> 00:09:13,900
Yes, could you wait inside for a while?

168
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:16,295
Oh, I see, that's the situation.

169
00:09:16,319 --> 00:09:21,168
Wait, we came all the way from Japan like he asked, and GACKT-sama isn't even here?

170
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:23,880
I'm sorry.

171
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:27,567
Alright then, we'll wait inside.

172
00:09:28,509 --> 00:09:32,438
This place really is incredible.

173
00:09:33,060 --> 00:09:38,544
Where is GACKT-sama, and what is he doing?

174
00:09:38,569 --> 00:09:43,880
Can you please wait for a second? I will contact GACKT-sama

175
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:49,973
While they got in touch with GACKT-sama, we secretly took a look around the mansion.

176
00:09:51,078 --> 00:09:57,532
The first thing that caught our eye was his trademark collection of sunglasses.

177
00:09:58,129 --> 00:10:02,033
Then a bunch of accessories that just scream 'expensive.'

178
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:07,206
And in his custom gym, where he trains every day,

179
00:10:07,230 --> 00:10:11,811
Here is GACKT-sama's original workout list.

180
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,616
You know what, let's sneak a look at the garage too.

181
00:10:16,641 --> 00:10:22,488
Inside were an Evangelion-themed Lamborghini and a Jaguar.

182
00:10:23,131 --> 00:10:25,625
Their emblems were sparkling bright.

183
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:29,795
After waiting for an hour,

184
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:31,065
Sorry to keep you waiting.

185
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:34,295
Yes, thank you for waiting.

186
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:39,495
Apparently GACKT is tied up and can't get away right now.

187
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,893
Tied up?

188
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,576
He asked to please come where he is instead.

189
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:47,869
Got it. Could you take us to where he is?

190
00:10:47,894 --> 00:10:49,382
Yes, of course.

191
00:10:49,407 --> 00:10:51,812
We appreciate it.

192
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:57,335
If he's that tied up, what exactly is he doing there?

193
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,442
He's doing something a bit dangerous.

194
00:10:58,467 --> 00:10:59,303
I see...

195
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:05,460
Something dangerous? Where on earth are they taking us?

196
00:11:07,038 --> 00:11:14,006
The thing he wants to discuss better not be not appearing on the show at all

197
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:21,113
Entertainer Ranking Check 2026.

198
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:26,619
The total value of the instruments used by the 8 piece orchestra will break the show's all-time record.

199
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:29,822
An astonishing 10.24 billion yen.

200
00:11:29,847 --> 00:11:32,540
The standout among them is this violin.

201
00:11:32,803 --> 00:11:34,800
The Stradivarius 'Corbett.'

202
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:38,064
This 'Corbett' has an exceptionally limited repair history.

203
00:11:38,089 --> 00:11:41,580
The condition of this original wood from 300 years ago

204
00:11:41,605 --> 00:11:43,515
has been preserved in the best possible state.

205
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:45,104
This will be shown in Japan for the very first time

206
00:11:45,129 --> 00:11:47,840
exclusively on this ranking check show.

207
00:11:47,865 --> 00:11:50,835
After three years of negotiations,

208
00:11:50,859 --> 00:11:52,625
it is finally making its Japan debut.

209
00:11:52,817 --> 00:11:55,555
It is the most expensive item in the show's history,

210
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:57,415
worth 2.5 billion yen.

211
00:11:57,439 --> 00:11:59,947
Here is how it sounds.

212
00:12:15,968 --> 00:12:18,437
There's no escape now.

213
00:12:18,462 --> 00:12:20,996
Damn, they totally outmaneuvered us.

214
00:12:29,949 --> 00:12:32,394
This time, eight teams are taking part.

215
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:33,652
Next up,

216
00:12:33,677 --> 00:12:37,698
Top idols who headline concerts at all five major domes,

217
00:12:37,723 --> 00:12:41,327
Kis-My-Ft2, celebrating their 15th anniversary.

218
00:12:41,352 --> 00:12:45,931
This time, the entire group is here together.

219
00:12:45,956 --> 00:12:48,343
The warm-up question for Kis-My-Ft2 is

220
00:12:48,368 --> 00:12:49,702
tsurume (dried squid).

221
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:52,267
And the answer they chose is...

222
00:12:52,995 --> 00:12:55,135
We're split.

223
00:12:55,159 --> 00:12:57,748
We're pretty much divided half and half.

224
00:12:57,774 --> 00:13:00,135
It's our first time on this show.

225
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,190
Yeah, it really is Takashi's first time.

226
00:13:02,215 --> 00:13:04,578
You can be the one to decide.

227
00:13:05,081 --> 00:13:06,568
B!

228
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:09,183
Boo!

229
00:13:11,318 --> 00:13:13,269
What a terrible start.

230
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:14,326
Takashi...

231
00:13:14,351 --> 00:13:17,772
When I watched this show on TV it looked so fun.

232
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:20,169
I get a lot of them right when watching.

233
00:13:20,194 --> 00:13:21,097
Seriously?

234
00:13:21,122 --> 00:13:23,602
That's what everyone watching at home says.

235
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:30,215
All six members of Kis-My-Ft2 join forces as one,

236
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:34,429
and pull off a miracle never before seen on this show.

237
00:13:34,453 --> 00:13:36,182
No way!

238
00:13:36,207 --> 00:13:38,484
That's amazing.

239
00:13:38,509 --> 00:13:41,020
Next,

240
00:13:41,045 --> 00:13:47,512
'Okome no Onna', a drama set in the National Tax Agency, starting Thursday, January 8,

241
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:55,634
and the human love mystery 'Saikai', starting Tuesday, January 13.

242
00:13:55,658 --> 00:13:59,871
First, Daichi Mao and Takeuchi Ryoma.

243
00:13:59,897 --> 00:14:03,142
Their warm-up question is about umeboshi (pickled plums).

244
00:14:03,167 --> 00:14:05,553
And the answer they gave is...

245
00:14:07,813 --> 00:14:13,641
This one was more sour, but in a refined way,

246
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:16,771
so I figured it had to be the more expensive one.

247
00:14:16,787 --> 00:14:17,804
Then A.

248
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:21,337
I'm sorry if I'm wrong.

249
00:14:21,362 --> 00:14:23,392
Brilliant   that's correct.

250
00:14:24,357 --> 00:14:27,366
Thank goodness.

251
00:14:27,391 --> 00:14:30,515
I want to stay top tier.

252
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:32,171
I want to go home with a pleasant feeling.

253
00:14:32,504 --> 00:14:34,245
Ryoma Takeuchi,

254
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:37,484
you're way too fired up for New Year's?!

255
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:39,584
I went with the taste, I guess.

256
00:14:39,609 --> 00:14:40,613
I focused on the flavor.

257
00:14:40,637 --> 00:14:43,454
Didn't you just get drunk on the red wine?

258
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,119
And lastly, from the world of entertainment,

259
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,720
our superstar veteran team.

260
00:14:47,963 --> 00:14:49,455
B.

261
00:14:50,906 --> 00:14:52,291
(eliminated. not worth showing)

262
00:14:52,316 --> 00:14:55,859
We have Emiko Kaminuma, who was eliminated last time,

263
00:14:55,884 --> 00:14:58,205
and YOSHIMI TENDO making her first appearance.

264
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:00,415
I left home today really pumped up for this.

265
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,634
I'm not kidding, for the past three days

266
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,315
I've been telling myself I'm going to be the last one standing.

267
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:05,838
I came here thinking my rival is GACKT.

268
00:15:05,862 --> 00:15:07,674
And I, too,

269
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:10,065
as a first-rate entertainer,

270
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:13,220
am here today with a lot of pride.

271
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:16,172
We're going to get every single question right.

272
00:15:16,184 --> 00:15:19,133
We've each been in show business for 50 years

273
00:15:19,145 --> 00:15:21,854
that's 100 years between us.

274
00:15:21,878 --> 00:15:26,760
Their warm-up question is beef heart.

275
00:15:27,576 --> 00:15:33,795
Hatsu is super common at yakiniku places in Kansai.

276
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:35,372
And the answer they gave is...

277
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,298
Are they the same?

278
00:15:39,005 --> 00:15:40,396
The depth of the flavor is different.

279
00:15:40,420 --> 00:15:42,215
Ah, they're different.

280
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,356
Okay.

281
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,315
We're done for.

282
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:50,320
From here?

283
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:51,163
From here?

284
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,285
From here

285
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,259
Tendo-saaan!

286
00:15:55,284 --> 00:15:56,322
It's okay.

287
00:15:56,346 --> 00:16:00,040
This legendary duo with over 100 years of showbiz experience between them

288
00:16:00,065 --> 00:16:02,337
runs wild all over the place!

289
00:16:02,361 --> 00:16:06,632
Why are you acting like the host?

290
00:16:06,656 --> 00:16:08,767
We're going to do something a bit dangerous now.

291
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:15,741
GACKT suddenly summons them to Malaysia for a meeting.

292
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:20,000
They drive off with his staff

293
00:16:20,803 --> 00:16:26,160
Without being told where they're going.

294
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:30,522
After 1 hour they're surrounded by untouched nature.

295
00:16:30,547 --> 00:16:34,626
After 2 hours they are deep into the mountains.

296
00:16:34,859 --> 00:16:41,000
What dangerous thing is GACKT doing out in a jungle like this?

297
00:16:43,602 --> 00:16:51,640
What on earth is he up to? He's not doing anything shady... right?

298
00:16:51,951 --> 00:16:56,081
After three hours in the car...

299
00:16:56,915 --> 00:16:58,275
'This way, please.'

300
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,215
Here?

301
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,419
Yes.

302
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:05,615
They're taken to a place where lots of dogs are wandering around,

303
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,394
a place that is clearly not normal by any stretch.

304
00:17:09,380 --> 00:17:10,995
Isn't this kind of sketchy?

305
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:12,355
It is sketchy.

306
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:14,600
Yeah, it definitely feels that way.

307
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:19,054
Please get on this boat.

308
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,035
Huh? We're getting on a boat?

309
00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:22,080
Where's GACKT?

310
00:17:23,034 --> 00:17:26,974
Once we get there, I think you'll be able to meet GACKT.

311
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:29,000
Is this boat actually safe?

312
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,585
It's fine.

313
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:33,185
What's your name?

314
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:35,233
Lei

315
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:39,224
Take care. I hope you get to him safely.

316
00:17:40,220 --> 00:17:43,328
This is where we say goodbye to GACKT's staff.

317
00:17:44,038 --> 00:17:48,899
From here, we head to GACKT on Mr. Lei's sketchy-looking boat.

318
00:17:48,926 --> 00:17:53,872
Fourteen hours from Japan, switching between plane, car, and boat.

319
00:17:53,897 --> 00:17:58,571
Where on earth is GACKT and what is he doing?

320
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:05,692
Ignoring our worries, Mr. Lei's boat heads deep into the jungle.

321
00:18:06,234 --> 00:18:09,069
There are wild animals along the shore.

322
00:18:09,098 --> 00:18:11,290
(cow)

323
00:18:12,421 --> 00:18:16,035
(monkey)

324
00:18:16,059 --> 00:18:17,269
(buffalo)

325
00:18:17,294 --> 00:18:23,602
According to Mr. Lei, even tigers and leopards live here. It's a place that basically shuts people out.

326
00:18:23,627 --> 00:18:26,495
Whoa, that beehive is huge.

327
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:29,555
Mr. Lei says one sting from those and you're dead.

328
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:33,429
Is GACKT really in a place this dangerous?

329
00:18:33,763 --> 00:18:37,966
We ride the boat for another hour.

330
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:42,946
Pushing through the bushes, we come to...

331
00:18:49,392 --> 00:18:52,096
Huh? There’s someone there.

332
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,485
That kinda looks like GACKT.

333
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:59,104
Nervously, we call out to him.

334
00:18:59,129 --> 00:19:01,715
Excuse me, are you GACKT?

335
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:03,470
Good morning.

336
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:07,504
I can't see his face, but he really seems like GACKT.

337
00:19:08,552 --> 00:19:11,415
That must've taken you a long time, right?

338
00:19:11,438 --> 00:19:14,614
It took us almost 14 hours.

339
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:20,815
Can we talk on the boat?

340
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:23,695
Over here. Yes.

341
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:26,155
This cool-looking boat?

342
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:27,555
Is this yours, GACKT?

343
00:19:27,580 --> 00:19:30,577
Yeah, it's mine.

344
00:19:30,602 --> 00:19:32,294
Sorry if this sounds rude, but...

345
00:19:32,319 --> 00:19:35,643
You really are GACKT, right?

346
00:19:35,668 --> 00:19:38,265
Long time no see.

347
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:39,671
Ouch!

348
00:19:39,696 --> 00:19:43,375
This firm handshake has got to be GACKT.

349
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,555
Could you maybe just show us your face, just to be sure?

350
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:47,845
I get sunburned, you know.

351
00:19:47,870 --> 00:19:50,235
See?

352
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:52,424
Ah, it really is GACKT.

353
00:19:53,279 --> 00:19:55,427
I told you, that hurts.

354
00:19:56,560 --> 00:20:00,799
By the way, GACKT, what are you doing all the way out here?

355
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:08,353
I was out fishing, but my car broke down and I couldn’t get back.

356
00:20:08,378 --> 00:20:12,707
So that’s why we couldn’t meet you at your place.

357
00:20:12,732 --> 00:20:15,280
That's right, I'm sorry.

358
00:20:15,305 --> 00:20:19,685
They just put us on a boat without telling us anything, and it took over an hour to get here.

359
00:20:19,710 --> 00:20:27,025
Nobody knows about this spot, not even the locals.

360
00:20:28,326 --> 00:20:30,495
So it's nice, no one bothers me out here.

361
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:34,208
What were you fishing for here?

362
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,842
A fish called toman.

363
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:36,694
Toman?

364
00:20:36,721 --> 00:20:41,439
Yeah, it's a fish called the giant snakehead.

365
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:45,594
Toman are snakehead fish that live widely across Southeast Asia.

366
00:20:45,618 --> 00:20:49,580
They're smarter than largemouth bass and much harder to catch.

367
00:20:50,081 --> 00:20:51,820
Is this lure fishing?

368
00:20:52,450 --> 00:20:53,376
Yeah, it is.

369
00:20:53,940 --> 00:20:56,215
When did you start?

370
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:59,603
I got hooked on it about three years ago.

371
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:04,363
And I've been coming out here ever since.

372
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:07,815
You need this many rods just to fish for toman?

373
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,815
This is all tackle.

374
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:14,473
They're all different types of rods.

375
00:21:14,498 --> 00:21:20,212
When we saw your house earlier, there was a crazy amount of fishing gear.

376
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:25,125
That’s not a shop, right?

377
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:26,475
No, it’s not.

378
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:30,589
I kept testing different things and it just piled up.

379
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:34,960
You’re an artist, so why are you so obsessed with fishing?

380
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:40,815
Right now, Japan’s fishing industry is in a slump.

381
00:21:40,840 --> 00:21:46,305
But Japanese tackle makers are still among the best in the world.

382
00:21:46,329 --> 00:21:52,443
So seeing the Japanese market shrink this much feels kind of sad, you know?

383
00:21:52,469 --> 00:21:55,681
So I started wondering if there was something I could do to support it.

384
00:21:55,706 --> 00:22:00,719
But if you’re not actually good at it, no one will take you seriously.

385
00:22:00,744 --> 00:22:02,788
That’s why I practice.

386
00:22:02,813 --> 00:22:08,126
Apparently, he’s working on some kind of fishing entertainment project.

387
00:22:08,151 --> 00:22:13,315
Here’s GACKT reeling in a toman.

388
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:16,034
Once he gets into something, GACKT takes it to the extreme.

389
00:22:16,059 --> 00:22:20,572
Now, they say he’s one of the top anglers in Malaysia when it comes to toman.

390
00:22:20,597 --> 00:22:27,946
Toman can grow to about 13 kilos and are dangerous enough to bite off a human finger.

391
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:31,483
Another thing that caught our eye was his bookshelf at home.

392
00:22:31,508 --> 00:22:38,390
It was lined with language books. How many languages can you speak now, GACKT?

393
00:22:38,415 --> 00:22:42,753
In Malaysia, English is the main language I use.

394
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:50,180
I’ve got a lot of Chinese friends too, so I speak Mandarin as well.

395
00:22:51,069 --> 00:22:57,101
And when I meet my Korean friends, I speak a bit of Korean.

396
00:22:57,180 --> 00:22:59,555
I also saw some French books.

397
00:22:59,580 --> 00:23:03,143
I haven’t used French at all lately.

398
00:23:03,660 --> 00:23:06,385
I’ve gotten rusty… or more like I’ve forgotten most of it.

399
00:23:06,409 --> 00:23:11,289
There were quite a few books about conversations between men and women, though.

400
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:15,267
What are you looking at those for?

401
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,662
Is that the easiest way to remember things?

402
00:23:17,687 --> 00:23:22,834
Well, you’re most motivated when it comes to flirting, right?

403
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:26,638
So, what kind of year was 2025 for you?

404
00:23:26,663 --> 00:23:32,294
 Let me think…

405
00:23:32,306 --> 00:23:39,351
it was a year of preparing to fully restart my music activities in 2026.

406
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:42,835
I was doing films and dramas and such.

407
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:46,132
But mostly, I spent the year laying the groundwork for music.

408
00:23:46,220 --> 00:23:50,529
From 2026, I’m really getting back into it.

409
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:54,608
So you already have concrete plans for your activities?

410
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:59,955
I’ll do a world tour, then head to South America.

411
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:05,452
And from March, I’ll start a project called 'LAST SONGS' with K.

412
00:24:11,316 --> 00:24:13,415
Wow, that’s insanely busy.

413
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:18,690
I’m really diving back into music again.

414
00:24:18,715 --> 00:24:20,895
My health is finally back to normal.

415
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:23,061
I’m really looking forward to that, seriously.

416
00:24:23,086 --> 00:24:29,815
You suddenly emailed saying you needed to talk, but what exactly about the Rating Check did you want to discuss?

417
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:30,880
That's right.

418
00:24:31,837 --> 00:24:37,375
Last year was pretty rough, wasn't it?

419
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:40,990
Yeah, on last year's Rating Check...

420
00:24:48,307 --> 00:24:52,107
Stupid tongue!

421
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:56,760
On the final question, because of my partner's huge blunder, we were eliminated.

422
00:24:57,480 --> 00:25:00,975
I knew it was going to end up like that.

423
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,975
GACKT's prediction was spot-on.

424
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,971
Even GACKT disappeared from the screen.

425
00:25:06,304 --> 00:25:10,355
So when you say you wanted to talk, is this about your partner?

426
00:25:10,379 --> 00:25:16,355
In 2026 I'll finally be restarting my music career,

427
00:25:16,452 --> 00:25:21,920
Who did GACKT pick for his partner?

428
00:25:21,945 --> 00:25:25,991
So who on earth is it?

429
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:32,764
Who is GACKT's partner this time?

430
00:25:32,789 --> 00:25:39,175
In 2026 I'll finally be restarting my music career,

431
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:44,429
and I kind of felt I didn't want anyone getting in my way.

432
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:49,115
I want to finish with a completely perfect score

433
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:55,697
and start off 2026 in the best possible way.

434
00:25:56,589 --> 00:26:00,883
So this time, I was thinking I would go in alone.

435
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:07,700
I was thinking of doing it by myself, and whether that was okay or not,

436
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:10,045
I wanted to get your judgment on that.

437
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:13,515
Last year really

438
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:16,942
stuck with me for months.

439
00:26:16,967 --> 00:26:19,590
I see, so it was like that for you.

440
00:26:19,614 --> 00:26:22,380
But taking it on alone is a pretty harsh choice, isn't it?

441
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:27,152
Of course I know it's going to be hard,

442
00:26:27,177 --> 00:26:31,275
but the hardest thing of all is relationships, right?

443
00:26:31,300 --> 00:26:33,395
Right now,

444
00:26:33,420 --> 00:26:36,460
when it comes to them,

445
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:38,735
I've kind of lost trust.

446
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:42,835
The thing is, we've already made offers to those two.

447
00:26:42,866 --> 00:26:45,009
Then let's have them on in 2027

448
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:47,715
Understood.

449
00:26:47,740 --> 00:26:49,695
If you're willing to go that far, GACKT,

450
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:52,655
then this time, let's have you go in alone.

451
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,435
All right, thank you very much.

452
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:56,395
Hey, I told you, that hurts!

453
00:26:56,418 --> 00:26:58,967
Thank you very much.

454
00:27:07,299 --> 00:27:26,520
Thank you for watching.

